records.addlTxt:
9:51 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by the Court - has received the petition for court appointed counsel.  Court makes statement regarding counsel.  Statement by defendant - will accept the DA's offer.  DA recites offer - upon plea to the charge, will recommend a fine and costs, AODA and DNA surcharge.  Defendant concurs.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

-$100 fine plus court costs - Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.
-AODA and any follow-up - to be completed within 60 days and proof to be filed with the COC and DA's office within the 60 days.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

Court adjourned at 9:57 a.m.

9:30 a.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant - will be getting an attorney, has filled out paperwork for court appointed counsel.  Court questions defendant regarding contacting any attorneys.  Statement by defendant - has not made contact with any attorneys.  Court instructs the defendant to contact at least 2 attorneys and why he can't afford them and can submit the info via writing to the court.  Upon receipt court will appoint.  Court questions defendant regarding payments.  Defendant can pay $100 per month towards attorney fees.  Court sets for Status Hearing on January 11, 2016 at 9:30 a.m.

Court adjourned at 9:34 a.m.
